# Commit Message Format:
# <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#
# Types:
#   data      - Add or update datasets
#   notebook  - Add or modify Jupyter notebooks
#   feat      - Introduce new functionality (e.g., model, metric)
#   fix       - Fix bugs or incorrect logic
#   refactor  - Code refactoring without behavior change
#   docs      - Documentation updates (including markdown or cell comments)
#   test      - Add or update tests or validation cells
#   chore     - Routine tasks, cleanup, renaming
#   infra     - Environment, configuration, dependency changes
#
# Scopes:
#   ingestion, preprocessing, feature, exploration, modeling,
#   evaluation, inference, utils, experiments, core
#
# Example:
# feat(modeling): add ensemble voting model with calibrated outputs
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Short summary (max 72 characters)
#
# Longer description (optional):
#
# - What was changed and why
# - Assumptions, dependencies, or limitations
# - Follow-up actions or TODOs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
